  "prompt": "Does Moto G4 support Reliance Jio 4G?",
  "response": "The Moto G4 does support 4G LTE, which includes compatibility with Reliance Jio's 4G network in India. However, one critical aspect to keep in mind is that Reliance Jio primarily uses Voice over LTE (VoLTE) for calls. The Moto G4 does not natively support VoLTE out of the box, which means that while you can use Jio for data services, you might not be able to make voice calls unless you use third-party apps like Jio4GVoice for calling over data. It's always a good idea to check for any software updates or confirm device compatibility for specific features with the carrier.",
